  "text": "The Envoy HTTP filter configuration propagation chain crosses two repositories. Step 1: In data-plane-api, the file envoy/extensions/filters/network/http_connection_manager/v3/http_connection_manager.proto defines the HttpConnectionManager protobuf message, which contains a 'repeated HttpFilter http_filters' field (field 5). The HttpFilter message (also in this proto, line 1339) has a name field and a config_type oneof (typed_config or config_discovery). Step 2: The router-specific proto at envoy/extensions/filters/http/router/v3/router.proto defines the Router message that configures the envoy.filters.http.router filter. Step 3: In envoy, source/extensions/filters/network/http_connection_manager/config.h defines HttpConnectionManagerFilterConfigFactory (which creates the network filter) and HttpConnectionManagerConfig (which maps the proto config to runtime config and implements FilterChainFactory). Step 4: HttpConnectionManagerConfig's constructor in source/extensions/filters/network/http_connection_manager/config.cc calls helper.processFilters(config.http_filters(), ...) to iterate through the repeated HttpFilter entries. Step 5: source/common/http/filter_chain_helper.h defines FilterChainHelper::processFilters which iterates each HttpFilter proto entry and uses the filter config provider manager to resolve the filter factory. Step 6: envoy/server/filter_config.h defines the NamedHttpFilterConfigFactory interface with createFilterFactoryFromProto(). Step 7: source/extensions/filters/http/common/factory_base.h provides the FactoryBase template that implements NamedHttpFilterConfigFactory by downcasting the proto to the specific config type and calling createFilterFactoryFromProtoTyped(). Step 8: source/extensions/filters/http/router/config.h defines RouterFilterConfig which extends FactoryBase<Router> and implements createFilterFactoryFromProtoTyped() in config.cc to create Router::ProdFilter instances.",
